<paragraph id="8A3936B02970FF8AFF07FB75FE9D64BA" blockId="2.[189,1400,1158,1223]" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">
<taxonomicName id="4D864D332970FF8AFF07FB75FD6264DD" authority="Amyot &amp; Serville, 1843: 490" authorityName="Amyot &amp; Serville" authorityPageNumber="490" authorityYear="1843" box="[189,645,1158,1185]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Hotinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B8F2EAA22970FF8AFF07FB75FEFC64DD" box="[189,283,1159,1184]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">Hotinus</emphasis>
Amyot &amp; Serville, 1843: 490
</taxonomicName>
. 
<typeStatus id="553D88122970FF8AFD2BFB75FD2B64DC" box="[657,716,1159,1185]" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">Type</typeStatus>
species: 
<taxonomicName id="4D864D332970FF8AFC81FB75FB0B64DC" authority="(Linnaeus, 1758)" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[827,1260,1158,1185]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Pyrops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="candelaria">
<emphasis id="B8F2EAA22970FF8AFC81FB75FBF064DD" box="[827,1047,1158,1184]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">Pyrops candelaria</emphasis>
(Linnaeus, 1758)
</taxonomicName>
by original designation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8A3936B02970FF8AFF07FB00FDC26571" blockId="2.[189,549,1266,1293]" box="[189,549,1266,1293]" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">
<heading id="D17181DC2970FF8AFF07FB00FDC26571" bold="true" box="[189,549,1266,1293]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="2" pageNumber="125" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B8F2EAA22970FF8AFF07FB00FDC26571" bold="true" box="[189,549,1266,1293]" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">
The 
<taxonomicName id="4D864D332970FF8AFF4FFB00FE916570" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[245,374,1266,1293]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Pyrops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="candelaria">
<emphasis id="B8F2EAA22970FF8AFF4FFB00FE916570" bold="true" box="[245,374,1266,1293]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">candelaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8A3936B02970FF8AFF07FAD6FBC16543" blockId="2.[189,1392,1316,1498]" box="[189,1062,1316,1343]" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">
The characters of this group mainly follow 
<bibRefCitation id="EE174B412970FF8AFD00FAD6FC426542" author="Baker C. F." box="[698,933,1316,1343]" pageId="2" pageNumber="125" pagination="343 - 364" refId="ref9803" refString="Baker C. F. 1925. Remarks on certain Indo-Malayan Fulgora, with special reference to Philippines species. Philippines Journal of Science 28: 343 - 364." type="journal article" year="1925">Baker’s (1925: 348)</bibRefCitation>
definition:
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C29C653B2970FF8BFF07FAB9FC3A63B5" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="126" pageId="2" pageNumber="125" type="description">
<paragraph id="8A3936B02970FF8AFF07FAB9FB5D65F0" blockId="2.[189,1392,1316,1498]" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">(1) cephalic process long and slender, usually strongly upcurved, sometimes oblique to nearly straight; (2) apex of cephalic process compressed laterally, rarely very slightly swelling at apex;</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8A3936B02970FF8AFF07FA6BFBDA65CE" blockId="2.[189,1392,1316,1498]" box="[189,1085,1433,1459]" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">(3) tegmina with transverse bands or transversely aligned spots or markings;</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8A3936B02970FF8AFF07FA32FDB565A7" blockId="2.[189,1392,1316,1498]" box="[189,594,1472,1498]" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">(4) hind wings variously coloured.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8A3936B02970FF8AFF07F9F7FDA46700" blockId="2.[187,1399,1541,1917]" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">
The group contains the 
<typeStatus id="553D88122970FF8AFE70F9F7FE1B6662" box="[458,508,1541,1567]" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">type</typeStatus>
species of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4D864D332970FF8AFD51F9F4FCDB6662" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1839" box="[747,828,1542,1567]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Pyrops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B8F2EAA22970FF8AFD51F9F4FCDB6662" box="[747,828,1542,1567]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">Pyrops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4D864D332970FF8AFCF1F9F4FC036662" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[843,996,1541,1567]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Pyrops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="candelaria">
<emphasis id="B8F2EAA22970FF8AFCF1F9F4FC036662" box="[843,996,1541,1567]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">P. candelaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and is the most species-rich group within the genus. 
<bibRefCitation id="EE174B412970FF8AFE2AF9DEFD46663A" author="Nagai S. &amp; Porion T." box="[400,673,1580,1607]" pageId="2" pageNumber="125" refId="ref11134" refString="Nagai S. &amp; Porion T. 1996. Fulgoridae 2: Catalogue illustre des Faunes asiatique et australienne. Sciences Nat, Compiegne." type="book" year="1996">Nagai &amp; Porion (1996)</bibRefCitation>
listed 25 species in the group and more recently a number of species were added: 
<taxonomicName id="4D864D332970FF8AFE0AF9A1FD3D6610" authority="(Distant, 1906)" authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Distant" baseAuthorityYear="1906" box="[432,730,1618,1645]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Pyrops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rogersi">
<emphasis id="B8F2EAA22970FF8AFE0AF9A1FDC66611" box="[432,545,1619,1644]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">P. rogersi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EE174B412970FF8AFD8AF9A0FD366610" author="Distant W. L." box="[560,721,1618,1645]" pageId="2" pageNumber="125" refId="ref10413" refString="Distant W. L. 1906. Rhynchota Vol. 3. Heteroptera-Homoptera. In: C. T. Bingham (ed.) The Fauna of British India, including Ceylon and Burma. Taylor and Francis, London. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 48423" type="book" year="1906">Distant, 1906</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
was transferred from the 
<taxonomicName id="4D864D332970FF8AFBB3F9A0FB4E6611" baseAuthorityName="Donovan" baseAuthorityYear="1800" box="[1033,1193,1618,1644]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Pyrops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pyrorhynchus">
<emphasis id="B8F2EAA22970FF8AFBB3F9A0FB4E6611" box="[1033,1193,1618,1644]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">pyrorhynchus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group by 
<bibRefCitation id="EE174B412970FF8AFF07F98BFE0A66EE" author="Constant J. &amp; Mohan A. V." box="[189,493,1657,1683]" pageId="2" pageNumber="125" pagination="1 - 24" refId="ref10257" refString="Constant J. &amp; Mohan A. V. 2017. The lanternflies from Andaman and Nicobar: one new Pyrops species, new records and illustrated key to the species (Hemiptera: Fulgoromorpha: Fulgoridae). Belgian Journal of Entomology 49: 1 - 24." type="journal article" year="2017">Constant &amp; Mohan (2017)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4D864D332970FF8AFE4DF988FC8666E9" authority="(Baker, 1925)" baseAuthorityName="Baker" baseAuthorityYear="1925" box="[503,865,1657,1684]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Pyrops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maquilinganus">
<emphasis id="B8F2EAA22970FF8AFE4DF988FD5966EE" box="[503,702,1657,1683]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">P. maquilinganus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EE174B412970FF8AFD76F98BFCBE66E9" author="Baker C. F." box="[716,857,1657,1684]" pageId="2" pageNumber="125" pagination="343 - 364" refId="ref9803" refString="Baker C. F. 1925. Remarks on certain Indo-Malayan Fulgora, with special reference to Philippines species. Philippines Journal of Science 28: 343 - 364." type="journal article" year="1925">Baker, 1925</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
was transferred from the 
<emphasis id="B8F2EAA22970FF8AFB3EF98BFB3366EE" box="[1156,1236,1657,1683]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">effusus</emphasis>
species group by 
<bibRefCitation id="EE174B412970FF8AFF5BF952FE4766C6" author="Constant J." box="[225,416,1696,1723]" pageId="2" pageNumber="125" pagination="1 - 23" refId="ref10108" refString="Constant J. 2015. Review of the effusus group of the Lanternfly genus Pyrops Spinola, 1839, with one new species and notes on trophobiosis (Hemiptera: Fulgoromorpha: Fulgoridae). European Journal of Taxonomy 128: 1 - 23. https: // doi. org / 10.5852 / ejt. 2015.128" type="journal article" year="2015">Constant (2015)</bibRefCitation>
and eight additional species were described: 
<taxonomicName id="4D864D332970FF8AFC07F953FB1666C7" authority="Constant, 2021" authorityName="Constant" authorityYear="2021" box="[957,1265,1696,1722]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Pyrops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="auratus">
<emphasis id="B8F2EAA22970FF8AFC07F953FBD266C7" box="[957,1077,1697,1722]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">P. auratus</emphasis>
Constant, 2021
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4D864D332970FF8AFB44F953FE16669C" authority="Constant &amp; Mohan, 2017" authorityName="Constant &amp; Mohan" authorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Pyrops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="azureus">
<emphasis id="B8F2EAA22970FF8AFB44F953FA9166C7" box="[1278,1398,1697,1722]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">P. azureus</emphasis>
